I’ve confirmed the two strongest bugs in code: `multicall` reuses `msg.value` across payable delegatecalls, and `refinanceLoan` rewrites the old lien to the new token without moving collateral. I’m now tightening the remaining candidates against the interface comments so the final merged list doesn’t mix intended design with exploitable behavior.
